<subSubSection id="5593C2B336832C519F939B24472879E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5532CE33A14D3C13752794806F819558" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="989DC52B5A782EF43786232A054C4F3C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="9C022634F7B6829C2777E2EBACBF65A1" authorityName="Murdock" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="de Vriese" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Ptisana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ptisana ternatea" order="Marattiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ternatea">
<emphasis id="94CEAD4C9F8EB09D42AFCF456E57254A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ptisana ternatea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(de Vriese) Murdock in having glabrous receptacles, synangia that do not extend to the apex of segments, pinnules gradually reducing in size toward the base of pinnae, and pinnule apices not abruptly acuminate. Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="BBAE1573A23C13D3CC2B68D736AD3EFB" authorityName="Murdock" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Kuhn" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Ptisana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ptisana melanesica" order="Marattiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="melanesica">
<emphasis id="2BAA8DC314EA4F217EA093244D80F92D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ptisana melanesica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Kuhn) Murdock in having larger pinnules with submarginal synangia and smaller marginal teeth. The marked variability in size of ultimate segments has not been recorded in any other 
<taxonomicName id="94F7752958B6621DEEA4BF895148FA9C" authorityName="A.G.G.Murdock" authorityYear="2008" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Ptisana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ptisana" order="Marattiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A6854A38D1C11979F10B038C6BEBB6A3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ptisana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6AD4104B5F2654D838C8C260CDAB8433" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="72C478DB34BFBF2D24A6A6FE0038BC1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE60FFD29F84EB9403D9B7B2347D16D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="3AE6CFF4745B38357D3402FDD9A7E38E" authority="var. decipiens" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Ptisana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ptisana decipiens subsp. var. var. decipiens" order="Marattiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="decipiens" subSpecies="var." variety="decipiens">Ptisana decipiens var. decipiens</taxonomicName>
: Fronds 3-pinnate, up to 2.5 m long. Stipe up to 1.2 m long, round in cross-section, surface green to brown, darkening with age, with reddish-blackish scales, the broader scales being darker in color, lenticels raised (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8B0EBEEA1866C981BB81020BD30B8EBA" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Ptisana decipiens var. decipiens: A type specimen, with characteristically large segments B stipe showing scales C adaxial surface of fertile segments, showing vein spacing, synangial distance from margin, and winged costa. Ptisana decipiens var. delicata: D type specimen, with characteristically small segments E abaxial surface of fertile segment with maturing synangia. Photos: C. - W. Chen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.170.59471.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/485322" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4B</figureCitation>
). Fronds bearing 3 pairs of similarly sized pinnae on mature fronds, the terminal pair forking dichotomously at the frond apex, each pinna up to 1 m long. Swollen pulvini present at the base of all segments, green, smooth. Ultimate segments 5-12 pairs per pinnule, alternating on the costulae, largest at apex of each pinnule, smaller at the base, ultimate segments 9-18 cm long 
<normalizedToken id="9B5F208357B13077B14713190440F6EC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2.5 cm wide, elliptic to oblong with an acuminate apex; pinnule costulae gently zigzagging and clearly winged between segments (Figs 
<figureCitation id="C24D85934FA3668058326F0DD4FB2E58" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Ptisana decipiens var. decipiens: A type specimen, with characteristically large segments B stipe showing scales C adaxial surface of fertile segments, showing vein spacing, synangial distance from margin, and winged costa. Ptisana decipiens var. delicata: D type specimen, with characteristically small segments E abaxial surface of fertile segment with maturing synangia. Photos: C. - W. Chen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.170.59471.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/485322" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="4751B55FDD29E6F52E0899B133DA3F5D" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Comparison of venation and margins (A-E) and apices of ultimate segments (F, G) of the Ptisana species in the Solomon Islands A, F P. ambulans B, G P. decipiens var. decipiens C, H P. decipiens var. delicata D, I P. papuana E, J P. smithii. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.170.59471.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/485324" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6G</figureCitation>
). Laminae herbaceous-coriaceous, dark green above, pale below, with sparse brown-orange scales along the veins and midrib abaxially. Veins free, ca. 1.3 mm apart, rarely dividing once near the midrib (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="467A58D8CBEA02E13EEA2C0E2236448C" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Comparison of venation and margins (A-E) and apices of ultimate segments (F, G) of the Ptisana species in the Solomon Islands A, F P. ambulans B, G P. decipiens var. decipiens C, H P. decipiens var. delicata D, I P. papuana E, J P. smithii. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.170.59471.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/485324" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6B</figureCitation>
). Leaf margin gently serrate, more conspicuous at apex. Synangia green when immature, brown after opening, one per vein, submarginal, set back from leaf margin by 1-2 mm, ca. 1.8 mm long 
<normalizedToken id="E1C4867B9025DCFDDAB4A59B8511E448" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8 mm wide, 14-20 locules per synangium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="87E834558D524FEC94978B1615792A49" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Ptisana decipiens var. decipiens: A type specimen, with characteristically large segments B stipe showing scales C adaxial surface of fertile segments, showing vein spacing, synangial distance from margin, and winged costa. Ptisana decipiens var. delicata: D type specimen, with characteristically small segments E abaxial surface of fertile segment with maturing synangia. Photos: C. - W. Chen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.170.59471.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/485322" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4C</figureCitation>
), receptacles glabrous.
</paragraph>
<caption id="E181646034324E8EEBFCE70E219AD90F" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.170.59471.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/485322" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="7EE4A82D17CF961A3A15488E2A43759D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="CED14AB8C58B8C3B5915F1A79AC934E6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4235CF84E962D3D7C8EE4FEF23DD61C3" authority="var. decipiens" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Ptisana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ptisana decipiens subsp. var. var. decipiens" order="Marattiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="decipiens" subSpecies="var." variety="decipiens">Ptisana decipiens var. decipiens</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis id="82C683593868AC6DACAB5DE42DA77D70" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
type specimen, with characteristically large segments 
<emphasis id="0037E287F5D23AA9E556E29EE13122EC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
stipe showing scales 
<emphasis id="A840727776087B96E0C2358182078A02" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C</emphasis>
adaxial surface of fertile segments, showing vein spacing, synangial distance from margin, and winged costa. 
<taxonomicName id="04C531E2B9991BC56804E62D01222121" authorityName="Murdock &amp; C. W. Chen" authorityYear="2020" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Ptisana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ptisana decipiens subsp. var. var. delicata" order="Marattiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="decipiens" subSpecies="var." variety="delicata">Ptisana decipiens var. delicata</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis id="03CDF5FE2555653F6535D204DBE178DD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D</emphasis>
type specimen, with characteristically small segments 
<emphasis id="467856D0E1A1A344A760AF176A1AA691" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E</emphasis>
abaxial surface of fertile segment with maturing synangia. Photos: C.-W. Chen.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9CF48CAE6A0EF49BEACE2F24B96DFBF2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="9BC970B6C2350432C50A954645E8563C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85932DFDC593E9D478BDF20EAF4A5539" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="6C8D8138F9A4E1AB4368DD39BDE5423D" authorityName="Murdock &amp; C. W. Chen" authorityYear="2020" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Ptisana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ptisana decipiens" order="Marattiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="BB0E762701509AA61B29A6B6DD9513C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ptisana decipiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(deceiving or misleading) refers to the morphological variation that has misled people into thinking two species were present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
